play; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> She went on to share her own theory as to why viewers would find it difficult to believe her as an American. “It&#39;s the teeth!” she claimed. “No Americans have my teeth. I think that genuinely is one of the things.”</p><p> “I played an American in a play in Chicago and afterwards this guy in the bar, he was talking to me and he went, &#39;I knew it, I knew it. Your accent was great but I knew you weren&#39;t American. You just don&#39;t look American&#39;.”</p><p> Wood recently spoke to <i>NME</i> about filming the show, describing the experience as “claustrophobic” and comparing it to <i>The Truman Show</i> – see the interview above.</p><p> The third season of HBO&#39;s black comedy series, which is set in a luxury hotel resort in Thailand, is airing every Sunday night in the US, with the fifth episode arriving tonight (March 16).</p><p> Episode four, meanwhile, included a much-discussed scene in which Jason Isaacs&#39; character Timothy is exposed in a full-frontal shot, with <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/the-white-lotus-fans-shocked-by-jason-isaacs-nude-scene-in-best-episode-of-season-so-far-3844921">fans on social media reacting with lewd jokes to the shocking sight</a> .</p><p> Isaacs himself <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/jason-isaacs-was-very-excited-about-the-white-lotus-nude-scene-3846462">was said to be “very excited” to shoot the scene</a> , but the actor has since <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/following-prosthetic-penis-debate-the-white-lotus-star-jason-isaacs-calls-out-double-standard-for-men-who-do-nude-scenes-3846495">called out what he considers to be gendered “double standards”</a> when nude scenes are discussed in the media.</p><p> “I think it&#39;s interesting that there&#39;s a double standard for men, but when women are naked, [like] Margaret Qualley in <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/the-substance"><i>The Substance</i></a> , no one would dream of talking to her about her genitalia or her nipples or any of those things. So, it&#39;s odd that there&#39;s a double standard,” he said.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/the-white-lotus-star-aimee-lou-wood-says-audiences-wouldnt-believe-her-as-an-american-its-the-teeth-3846674">&#39;The White Lotus&#39; star Aimee Lou Wood says audiences wouldn&#39;t believe her as an American: “It&#39;s the teeth!”</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
